Salem Al-Tamimi

Saint John, NB | Halifax, NS

Also known as: saltamimi

Salem Al-Tamimi came to RapidMind Solutions after holding several positions within the IT industry, serving clients around the world from North America, to Europe and the Middle East. He is passionate about finding the best solution to complex problems and implementing it in the most efficient way possible. He has developed a reputation with his co-workers as a skilled software developer who is always looking to improve himself through learning. He shares his knowledge with his colleagues and often takes the role of a mentor or advisor to help others. Salem is quick to take on responsibility within a team and holds himself personally accountable for meeting his deadlines and obligations. He has experience working with many different team configurations from solo work to a team of 20+ members. He works primarily with the Microsoft Suite of development products and languages including Visual Studio, VB.NET, C#, ASP.NET, SQL Server, MS Access, and SharePoint. In the past 3 years, he has been focusing on SharePoint development and administration. Salem is always looking for a new challenge. He enjoys writing code and producing software both professionally and for fun. He has developed a site for online creativity and collaboration that boasts a following of 20,000+ people from around the world. When heâ€™s not writing code he loves to travel the world; his favorite vacation spots are Prince Edward Island (Canada), Dubai (UAE), Veradero (Cuba), and London (England). Specialties Problem solving, taking on major responsibilities, mentoring, continuous learning, Systems Analysis, SharePoint & .NET development, databases, security, management, all aspects of developing online/multiplayer RPGs

Salem F. Al-Qassimi

Providence, RI | New York, NY

Also known as: salqass

Salem Al-Qassimi is a graphic designer and entrepreneur born and raised in Sharjah, United Arab Emirates (UAE). He received a Bachelor of Science degree in Multimedia Design from the American University of Sharjah (AUS), and a Master of Fine Arts in Graphic Design from the Rhode Island School of Design (RISD), during which he also served as a teaching assistant and instructor. His thesis was an investigation of the Arabish (Arabic and English) culture in the United Arab Emirates. Salem worked at various companies in the UAE and abroad before founding Fikra in a multidisciplinary design studio that specializes in providing bilingual graphic design solutions in Arabic and English. Fikra works in print and new media, including identity creation, book design, environmental graphics, data-visualizations, interaction design, web design, and motion graphics. The studios philosophy is deeply rooted in exploring the intersections of cultural Arabic and Islamic traditions and modern lifestyle through design. While practicing, Salem also teaches design studios at the American University of Sharjah in the College of Architecture, Art and Design. Salem is based in Sharjah, UAE, and New York, USA.
